HEADWORD: Loretto nuns
<hw>Lo*ret"to
nuns</hw> <pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>. <ety>[From <etsep>Loreto</etsep>, a city
in Italy famous for its Holy House, said to be that in which Jesus
lived, brought by angels from Nazareth.]</ety> <fld>(R. C. Ch.)</fld>
<def>Members of a congregation of nuns founded by <person>Mrs. Mary
Teresa Ball</person>, near Dublin, Ireland, in 1822, and now spread over
Ireland, India, Canada, and the United States. The nuns are called also
<altname>Ladies of Loreto</altname>. They are engaged in teaching
girls.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lorette</ent>⟦br⟧
